To the examples of water and honey Lucr. now adds others: a mere breath will upset a heap of poppy·seed, because the sends are smooth and round, but will have no effect on a heap of pebbles or ears of corn, because the pebbles are heavy and the ears os corn are rough and stick together. Giussani, with great probability, refers the simile to games still played by Italian children, in which they pile up poppy- seed on the hand, and swallow it, the difficulty being to help blowing it away.
